Stephen Hensley

Born about 1793 in Virginia, United States

Ancestors

Son of Christopher Chrisley Hensley and Catherine (Tompkins) Davis

Husband of Mary Nancy (Farley) McGinnis — married 19 Apr 1814 in Cabell, West Virginia, United States

Father of Stephen M Hensley

Died about 1842 at about age 49 in Virginia, United States

Profile last modified 8 May 2023 | Created 7 Jan 2021

This page has been accessed 241 times.

This profile lacks source information. Please add sources that support the facts.

Biography

Stephen was born about 1793. He was the son of Christopher Chrisley Hensley and Catherine Tompkins.

July 1, 1817, he received a grant of 120 acres of land on the Big Fork of Sandy River in Cabell County, Virginia, beginning about 20 poles below the trace that comes over from the head of Grape Vine.

He passed away about 1842. [1]
